<p>Laurence des Cars, director of the Louvre in Paris, told a Senate committee she had offered to resign after a daylight theft stole about €88 million in crown jewels from the museum and exposed weaknesses in its external camera coverage [aljazeera.com#1][dawn.com#1][thehindu.com#2]. Des Cars said alarms had worked but the key exterior camera was pointed away from the balcony used by the thieves, and she conceded perimeter surveillance was &quot;highly insufficient&quot; [dawn.com#1][bbc.com#1]. The museum reopened to visitors with the Galerie d&#x27;Apollon closed while President Emmanuel Macron ordered an acceleration of security measures at the Louvre as the investigation continues [thehindu.com#2][dw.com#1][dawn.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/j1nCggUHoKqUOf9V9nz6z_P5clG4wmpdsIhvN7oHRusQMHz8-njRcgtx21fNim1XuPmtG-6woTx32GvvEwR_gc_JEaPdbUzisUOuvs8WlJqr' alt='President of the Louvre Museum Laurence des Cars looks on prior to the start of a hearing before the Senate’s culture committee at the French Senate in Paris on October 22, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Senate grilling: Des Cars faced nearly three hours of questioning before the Sénat&#x27;s culture committee, where she said the theft &quot;was not inevitable&quot; and outlined security shortcomings [lemonde.fr#1][aljazeera.com#1]</li><li>Precious losses: Among the eight stolen pieces were an emerald-and-diamond necklace given by Napoleon I to Empress Marie‑Louise and Empress Eugénie&#x27;s diadem, the latter studded with nearly 2,000 diamonds, raising both cultural and restoration concerns [dawn.com#1]</li><li>What worked: Museum officials told senators that building alarms functioned during the break-in, even though camera coverage failed to capture the point of entry [dawn.com#1]</li><li>Restoration outlook: Officials said a damaged diamond-and-emerald crown recovered at the scene can be restored, offering a positive sign for conserving at least some of the pieces [france24.com#1]</li><li>Government response: The culture ministry declined Des Cars&#x27;s resignation and President Macron ordered a speeding up of planned security upgrades at national museums, increasing scrutiny of museum protection nationwide [dawn.com#1][thehindu.com#2]</li></ul><blockquote>Despite our efforts, despite our hard work on a daily basis, we failed - Laurence des Cars</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Laurence des Cars (Louvre director): She acknowledged the museum&#x27;s failure but defended an ongoing €80-million security plan, disputing reports of &#x27;persistent delays&#x27; while offering her resignation to take responsibility [dawn.com#1][lemonde.fr#1]. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1950692/louvre-director-admits-insufficient-camera-coverage'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>French presidency (Emmanuel Macron): The president ordered that security measures at the Louvre be &#x27;sped up&#x27; as the museum reopened to visitors, signalling a national-level response to the breach [thehindu.com#2]. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/frances-macron-orders-tighter-security-as-louvre-reopens-doors/article70191053.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>Interior Minister Laurent Nunez: The minister said the investigation is progressing and provided reassurances that authorities are pursuing leads in the rapid, daytime theft [dawn.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1950692/louvre-director-admits-insufficient-camera-coverage'>Dawn</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c9d6e2wv884o'>No camera covered Louvre wall where jewel thieves broke in, director says</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/23/louvre-director-recognises-jewel-theft-failures-says-she-offered-to-resign'>Louvre director recognises jewel theft failures, says she offered to resign</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/louvre-director-acknowledges-failure-after-jewel-hei